'''NOPEC''' is an informal expression sometimes used to refer to the set [[Chart of exports and production of oil by nation|List of Oil Exporting Nations not in OPEC|oil exporting nations not in OPEC]]. At various times, mainly during times of supply crisis in the Middle East, this set of nations have reduced OPEC's power as a cartel. In 2005, NOPEC represented approximately 50% of petroleum exports. The most significant among these are Russia, Norway and Mexico.

